TITLE: NY homeowner accused of fatally shooting woman who pulled into wrong driveway blamed 'hunters': court docs
SUMMARY: The New York man charged in the murder of a woman who was shot after the driver of a car she was in pulled into the wrong address blamed hunters for the shooting.

TITLE: Pennsylvania bear that attacked two young children captured, euthanized: officials
SUMMARY: A bear that attacked and injured two children last week in Pennsylvania was captured and euthanized as a precaution, according to officials.

TITLE: Georgia high school soccer coach arrested for allegedly molesting a child
SUMMARY: A Georgia high school soccer coach was arrested for allegedly molesting a child under the age of 10 when she was spending the night at his family's home.

TITLE: New Mexico shooting leaves 3 dead, 5 injured during Memorial Day weekend motorcycle rally
SUMMARY: Two people were killed and six others were injured in a shooting at an annual motorcycle rally in Red Rock, New Mexico, police said.

TITLE: Massachusetts man charged with bludgeoning neighbor, 58, to death held without bail
SUMMARY: Dinis Moreira of Bridgewater, Massachusetts, is being held without bail after he allegedly beat his neighbor, Valerie Oakhem, 58, to death with a hammer.

TITLE: Jordan Neely death: Family will file wrongful death lawsuit against Daniel Penny: Report
SUMMARY: Jordan Neely's family will file a wrongful death lawsuit against Daniel Penny, who allegedly fatally choked the homeless man on an NYC subway train on May 1.

TITLE: Climate activists indicted for smearing paint on Degas sculpture case at National Gallery
SUMMARY: Timothy Martin and Joanna Smith face federal charges for allegedly defacing the case of a Degas ballet dancer sculpture during a climate protest last month.

TITLE: Aliens 'have been on Earth a long time': Stanford Professor
SUMMARY: Dr. Garry Nolan, a pathology professor at Stanford University, said, "Aliens have been on Earth for a long time" and sent "intermediaries" to collect intelligence

TITLE: Louisiana high school grad still lost at sea after Coast Guard calls off search: report
SUMMARY: Cameron Robbins, 18, was celebrating high school graduation on a cruise in the Bahamas when he reportedly went overboard. The Coast Guard called off the search.

TITLE: Sealed Alex Murdaugh crime scene videos mistakenly sent to Netflix: report
SUMMARY: Video evidence from Alex Murdaugh's crime scene was mistakenly sent to Netflix, which required a judge's intervention in order to keep them sealed.

TITLE: Funeral director pleads guilty to theft after Indiana police discover 48 people's remains
SUMMARY: A funeral director in Jeffersonville, Indiana pleaded guilty to charges of theft after it was discovered he had failed to properly dispose of bodies.

TITLE: Weather officials warn Memorial Day beachgoers of dangerous rip currents along coasts
SUMMARY: While people flock to beaches across the U.S. this Memorial Day Weekend, forecasters at the National Weather Service warn of life-threatening rip currents.

TITLE: Senior man found dead on Utah national park trail
SUMMARY: A 69-year-old man was found dead on a trail at Arches National Park in Utah. Previous deaths were reported by the National Park Service in February and March.

TITLE: Ohio mother burned alive by ex-boyfriend testified at her own murder trial, doc reveals: ‘Pure evil'
SUMMARY: Judy Malinowski, a young mother from Ohio and a cancer survivor, testified from beyond the grave. Ex-boyfriend Michael Slager is serving a life sentence.

TITLE: Florida couple arrested in ‘bone chilling’ child abuse case, special needs 3-year-old 'rotting in bed': Police
SUMMARY: A Florida couple was charged with aggravated manslaughter after their special-needs 3-year-old son died under their care from alleged severe abuse.

TITLE: Virginia middle school students created 'fight club,' with some parents hosting: principal
SUMMARY: Students at a middle school in Virginia have started "fight clubs" that involve brackets, betting and challenges, the principal said in a letter.

TITLE: Maine woman brings raccoon to Petco for unconventional pet spa experience
SUMMARY: Wildlife officials in Maine are looking for woman who brought a wild raccoon to Petco for a nail trim even though it is illegal to possess wildlife in the state.

TITLE: Multi-state operation locates 225 missing children: US Marshals
SUMMARY: The United States Marshals Service, located 225 critically endangered missing children during a 10-week operation involving states across the US.

TITLE: Georgia father convicted of attempted rape of underage daughter
SUMMARY: A Georgia man will spend 40 years behind bars after a jury found him guilty of sexually assaulting his underage daughter. The girl reported the incident to law enforcement.

TITLE: Uvalde School Shooting: One year later
SUMMARY: Parents of Robb Elementary School shooting victims say one year later the town of Uvalde, Texas is still waiting for justice and accountability.

TITLE: Popular Chicago beach closed just hours after opening for summer when shots fired during fight
SUMMARY: A Chicago beach temporarily shut down just hours after it was opened for the summer season after shots were fired Friday afternoon when a fight broke out.

TITLE: Maryland girl, 14, speaks out after being shot in the head during drive-by shooting: ‘I almost lost my life’
SUMMARY: A Maryland teenager was allegedly shot in the head by a stray bullet during a drive-by shooting while she was outside a friend's apartment after school.

TITLE: MA diocese settles with ex-altar boy who accused long-deceased bishop of rape
SUMMARY: The Diocese of Springfield, Massachusetts, has settled with an unnamed plaintiff who credibly claimed Bishop Christopher Weldon sexually abused him six decades ago.

TITLE: Little Rock charter school system welcomes new CEO
SUMMARY: Career educator Cherie Labat has been selected to be the next CEO of Arkansas' eStem Public Charter School system, which serves nearly 3,000 students in Little Rock.

TITLE: Missing Texas soldier found alive after wife's death days earlier, Army says
SUMMARY: A Texas soldier missing for almost two weeks has been found alive, days after his wife died, Army officials said
